# ExpenseFlow Project Rules

## Auto-apply Instructions

When coding BACKEND:

- Read and follow: docs/backend-instrucstion.md
- Use INTEGER enums (1,2,3) in src/common/constants/enums.ts
- Entity columns: type: 'smallint' for enums
- DTO validation: @IsInt(), @Min(), @Max() for enum fields

When coding FRONTEND:

- Read and follow: docs/frontend-instrucstion.md
- Use INTEGER enums in src/constants/enums.ts
- Type naming: IUser, IProps, TType, TPaginated<T>
- Path aliases: @hooks, @redux, @services, @utils

## Enum Consistency

Backend and Frontend MUST use same integer enum values.
Example: AccountType.CASH = 1 (both FE & BE)
